This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic similarity, which are core topics in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also presents algorithms that take advantage of taxonomic similarity, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses resolving syntactic and semantic ambiguity, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
